    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Anonymous, these reheat pretty well.  I&#8217;ve never intentionally made them ahead of time, but when I have leftovers and reheat them the next day, they&#8217;re still pretty wonderful.   So yes, you can do that.  If I were you, I&#8217;d reheat them in a low oven, in a dish covered with foil.  </></>Or, you could just get your ingredients all prepped and measured and take them with you and cook them there.  This dish is pretty fast, really, and for most of its cooking time, you can just leave it alone.  Keep that in mind too.</></>Happy Thanksgiving!</p>
    </div>

